The only thing that's really tripped me up while upgrading our source to use 3.0.0 are some of the array methods on wrapped values. In particular, things that modify the wrapped value, like `push()` and `splice()`. This isn't a defect or anything, I just figured I should put in somewhere for those running into similar issues since their usage is slightly different than 2.4.1.

``` javascript

// Works as expected in 2.4.1...
var coll = _([ 1, 2, 3 ]);
coll.push(4);
coll.value();
// → [1, 2, 3, 4]

// However in 3.0.0...
var coll = _([ 1, 2, 3 ]);
coll.push(4);
coll.value();
// → [1, 2, 3]

// Which is because push() has no value() call, forcing it to run.
// So if it's not part of a longer chain, you need to manually call it...
var coll = _([ 1, 2, 3 ]);
coll.push(4).value();
coll.value();
// → [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

